         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 7/10/73. ¶  ¶ I was pleasingly surprised, dear Mr Berthoud, when I got your photogram, which I will put into the long series of autographed card-portraits of naturalists in my Album. ¶ The...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">73.10.07</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Berthoud</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Library, Royal Botanic Gardens, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">7/10/73.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was pleasingly surprised, dear Mr Berthoud, when I got your photogram, which I will put into the long series of autographed card-portraits of naturalists in my Album.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The photograph, made by Bent photographers, Sandhurst (later Bendigo, Vic) remains in M's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>surviving<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>album<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in the library, Royal Botanic gardens Melbourne.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As regards Insects I can do little for you myself, but a young Gardener in the Department here, Mr French,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Charles French Snr.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>studies them since years enthusiastically, and might give you much information on the native species.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In reference to plants I would remark that even new discoveries might be made by you, if you collect the rushes and sedges and such like plants, including all the smaller sorts; also any kind of water plants, even the minute sorts, but you must always endeavour to get the fruit</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The petal enclosed in your letter is from an Iris, which however is immigrated</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You should dry two sets of plants, number both correspondingly and keep one set, while you forward an other. I can then give you the names. Dont look for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fine</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>plants. Every collector picks them up. The less conspicuous kinds are those, which I yet need from the Campaspe.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Campaspe River, Vic.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have no photogram left of mine, but will send one hereafter.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A friend in Germany wants freshwater shells, especially minute sorts. So if you find any, please secure them for me.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: true; "
               xml:lang="en">Iris</p>
         </div>
      </body>
